### Code

```Rust
#![allow(unused)]
pub trait Temp {
    fn a(data: Self, data: Self);
}

/*impl Temp for i64 {
    fn a(data: Self, data: Self) {}
}*/
fn main() {

}
```


### Current output

```Shell
No output
```


### Desired output

```Shell
fn a(data: Self, data: Self) {}
                 ^^^^ used as parameter more than once
```


### Rationale and extra context

The above code complies successfully with no errors. But when I use the trait in the impl block I get the error that the parameter is used more than once. 

The reason this error is required is so that if libraries export such a trait then it wont be caught unless its used by the dependents.

